---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { BRAND } from '../config/brand';
---
<Base title="Security" path="/security/" description={`How ${BRAND.name} protects your family's data.`}>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <span class="eyebrow">Trust</span>
      <h1>Private by design.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Your family's financial life is some of the most sensitive information you have.
        Here's plainly how {BRAND.name} protects it — and what we don't yet claim.
      </p>
      <p class="updated">Last updated June 2026</p>

      <h2>What we do today</h2>

      <h3>Your vault is isolated to you</h3>
      <p>
        Every request is checked against your account. Your records are scoped to your vault and
        verified for ownership before anything is returned — one user's data is never served to
        another.
      </p>

      <h3>You control every share, and you can revoke it</h3>
      <p>
        Nothing is shared unless you grant it. When you create a referral package or share with a
        professional, you choose what's included, and consent is recorded with a clear scope. You
        can revoke access at any time, and the revocation is tracked.
      </p>

      <h3>We keep an audit trail</h3>
      <p>
        Key actions on your vault are recorded — what happened, when, and on which vault — so
        there's an accountable history of access and changes.
      </p>

      <h3>Your sign-in is protected</h3>
      <p>
        Passwords are hashed with scrypt and verified using a timing-safe comparison. We never
        store your password in plain text.
      </p>

      <h3>Document links are time-limited</h3>
      <p>
        When you open or share a stored document, access runs through a short-lived signed link
        that expires — links don't live forever.
      </p>

      <h3>We don't sell your data</h3>
      <p>
        Your vault exists to serve you and the people you choose to share it with. We do not sell
        your personal or financial data.
      </p>

      <h2>What we don't claim (yet)</h2>
      <p>
        We'd rather be honest than impressive. Today we do <strong>not</strong> claim
        application-level encryption-at-rest, "bank-grade" or "military-grade" encryption, or any
        third-party security certification (such as SOC 2 or ISO). As we add and independently
        validate further protections, we'll update this page — and we'll only say what's true.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy or security questions, contact us at
        <a href={`mailto:${BRAND.email.privacy}`}>{BRAND.email.privacy}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
